                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Umehara, M., Hanada, A., Yoshida, S. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Inhibition of shoot branching by new terpenoid plant hormones.</span> <span class='so'>Nature, 455, 195-200 (2008)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18690207" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Gomez-Roldan, V., Fermas, S., Brewer, P. B. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Strigolactone inhibition of shoot branching.</span> <span class='so'>Nature, 455, 189-194 (2008)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18690209" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Akiyama, K., Matsuzaki, K. & Hayashi, H.</span>: <span class="ti">Plant sesquiterpenes induce hyphal branching in arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi.</span> <span class='so'>Nature, 435, 824-827 (2005)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15944706" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Mouchel, C. F. & Leyser, O.</span>: <span class="ti">Novel phytohormones involved in long-range signaling.</span> <span class='so'>Curr. Opin. Plant Biol., 10, 473-476 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17884716" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Davis, S. J., Kurepa, J. & Vierstra, R. D.</span>: <span class="ti">The <em>Arabidopsis thaliana</em> HY1 locus, required for phytochrome-chromophore biosynthesis, encodes a protein related to heme oxygenases.</span> <span class='so'>Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 96, 6541-6546 (1999)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10339624" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Muramoto, T., Kohchi, T., Yokota, A. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">The <em>Arabidopsis</em> photomorphogenic mutant <em>hy1</em> is deficient in phytochrome chromophore biosynthesis as a result of a mutation in a plastid heme oxygenase.</span> <span class='so'>Plan